\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. T. cinerariifolium} (Trev.) Schultz Bip.,{\i  Tanacet.} 58 (1844) ({\i Pyrethrum cinerariifolium }Trev.). Caespitose, silvery-grey, sericeous perennial. Stems 15-45 cm. Leaves pinnatipartite, glandular-punctate; basal 10-20 cm, petiolate, lanceolate to oblong, the segments pinnatisect to palmatisect, narrowly lanceolate to oblong-lanceolate; cauline similar but shortly petiolate. Capitula solitary; involucre 12-18 mm. Ligulate florets white, female; ligules 8-16 mm. Achenes 2·5-3·5 mm, 5- to 7-ribbed. Pappus an irregularly lobed corona 0·6-1 mm.{\i  Rocky ground. W. Jugoslavia and Albania; cultivated elsewhere in S.E. & E. C. Europe as an insecticide, and locally naturalized.} Al Ju [Au Hs Hu It Rs (W, K, E)].
