\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs. Leaves simple, strongly glandular-punctate alternate. Capitula in a corymbose inflorescence. Involucral bracts in several rows. Receptacle plano-convex. Outer florets female, tubular or with white ligules, rarely absent. Inner florets hermaphrodite, tubular-obconical. Achenes all similar, 5- to 8-ribbed, with epicarpic non-mucilaginous glands; mucilage-cells and vallecular resin-canals absent; pappus short, irregularly toothed or lobed.
